Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil a large #pot{} of salted water for the potatoes.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{3} into 2cm chunks.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until fork tender, ~{15-20%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pot, off the heat.

Meanwhile, quarter the @onion{1}, then separate the layers. Pop the onion layers onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and @balsamic vinegar{1%sachet} then season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until softened, ~{15-20%mins}.

Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @parsley{5%g} (stalks and all).

Use a #fork{} to mash @butter{2%tbsp} (double for 4) in a #bowl{} until soft. Stir in the garlic and parsley. Set aside.

Season the @Irish beef rump{250%g} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Place a large pan over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

When the oil is hot, fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%mins} each side for medium-rare.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Cook for ~{1-2%mins} more each side for medium and an additional ~{1-2%mins} each side for well-done.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} and top with the parsley butter. Cover and leave to rest. Meat is safe to eat when outside is browned.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, add the broccoli to the pan and fry for ~{2-3%mins}, then add a splash of @water{to taste}.

Pop a #lid{} (or some #foil{}) on the pan, and cook until tender, ~{4-5%mins}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, mash the cooked potatoes with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @?water{to taste} or @?milk{to taste}. Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Divide the creamy mashed potato between your plates.

Serve the broccoli and roasted onion alongside.

Slice the beef rump and plate with the melted garlic parsley butter drizzled over.